{"title":"Shout","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Shout","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.22](/0.22 \"0.22\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n**Shouting** is an ability intrinsic to every playable [species](/Species \"Species\") and most [monsters](/Monsters \"Monsters\"). It allows the shouter to call attention to themselves and is an option found under the **[t](/T \"T\")** key.\n\nA character’s shout normally has a loudness of 12[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1), roughly equal to the loudest melee attacks and roughly half as loud as a [scroll of noise](/Scroll_of_noise \"Scroll of noise\"). Keep in mind that in some [branches](/Branch \"Branch\"), sounds such as shouting may travel more or less distance. More information can be found in the [noise](/Noise \"Noise\") article.\n\nMonsters (and players) shout to awaken and draw forth sleeping or wandering monsters nearby. A player might do this to force an enemy to open a door or to draw a few monsters from a crowd at a time, though shouting from the wrong position may bring an army down on you. Monsters who can shout often do so the moment they become aware of you; if you're concerned about the possibility of reinforcements, you may wish to retreat from enemies that shout near unexplored areas, luring the shouter away from anything that may have heard its cry. Also, bear in mind that your attacks and spells are often noisy in and of themselves.\n\nNote that you can command [summoned](/Summon \"Summon\") or [charmed](/Charm \"Charm\") allies silently, without alerting hostile monsters out of line of sight.\n\nShouting is impossible if the player or monsters are affected by [silence](/Silence \"Silence\").\n\nLike most in-game tactics, the benefits of shouting are situational. It is rarely something that [stealthy](/Stealth \"Stealth\") [stabbing](/Stabbing \"Stabbing\")-focused characters will want to do, while worshipers of [Ashenzari](/Ashenzari \"Ashenzari\") and characters with access to [telepathy](/Telepathy \"Telepathy\") or the [antennae](/Antennae \"Antennae\") mutation can often use it to great effect.\n\n## History\n\nPrior to [0.19](/0.19 \"0.19\"), ally commands weren't silent. Also, the player couldn't command allies while [Silenced](/Silence \"Silence\").\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [player.cc:5501](https://github.com/crawl/crawl/blob/0.22.0/crawl-ref/source/player.cc#L5501) (0.22.0)\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Shout - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Shout\",\"wgTitle\":\"Shout\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":49632,\"wgRevisionId\":49632,\"wgArticleId\":6727,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"0.22 articles\",\"Gameplay\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Shout\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":6727,\"wgRequestId\":\"5b6ae5b086bf743c8afc9b23\",\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[]});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"u